content: I think i may have solved the problem. I went into File > Get New Messages for > and the account was listed there... When I selected it TB DID now ask me for the Password and when I entered it (and ticked the "Store" it in Saved Passwords box) TB fetched the unread mails from the server and the account now appears in the Saved Passwords list with a pop3 entry too! TB now seems to be checking that server again now too when I click the "Get Messages" button. (However, there does seem to be some kind of flaw in the program that the Developers might wish to address here?)
creator: wb.cameron

content: Update: - after editing and sending out such a new message the original message will be disappear in the inbox. - just found a workaround: when open a new message by right mouse click "open in new tab" the message in the new tab will be fault free.
